bug.short_desc: The change to classListFromIncludeIterative in r27799 breaks dependency resolution in our codebase

long_desc.thetext:
This may be related to bug 4860 ...
We have a larger codebase, so it's kinda hard to track down exactly what isn't getting caught and why. If you need any more info let me know and I'll gladly get you what you need.
It looks like either the MessageBus isn't ever getting called in our codebase after running a generate.py source -- it's called in async RPC callbacks, and isn't getting fired. Running an "svn up -r 27798 tool/pylib/generator/code/DependencyLoader.py" resolves the issue on current versions of qooxdoo ( revision 27808 )
I don't know nearly enough about the tooling stuff to even know what info would help you guys resolve this, let me know what I can do to provide enough information.

(In reply to comment #1) > This may be related to bug 4860 ...
No, not really, but rather to bug#2366, as mentioned in the commit message of r27799.
> > We have a larger codebase, so it's kinda hard to track down exactly what isn't > getting caught and why. If you need any more info let me know and I'll gladly > get you what you need.
Yes, that would be great. For a start, could you run the generator on your project with the -v option, with both a version of DependencyLoader before and after the breakage, capture the output of both, and pass it to me. If you don't want to attach it to this bug, you can send it to me directly.
Thanks.

The offending function, DependencyLoader.classlistFromClassIterative, is not in use anymore. Maybe this bug has to be re-opened when I start working on it again. But 'till then it's probably not worth investing effort into it, without a failing sample for the current code base.
